quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
  21,45,"Say, “I only warn you by divine revelation.” But the deaf cannot hear the call when they are warned.",""
  21,46,"If a mere breath of your Lord’s torment were to touch them, they would surely say, “Woe to us! We were indeed wrongdoers.”",""
  21,47,"We will place the scales of justice on the Day of Resurrection, and no soul will be wronged in the least. Even if a deed is the weight of a mustard seed<sup>18</sup>, We will bring it forth. Sufficient are We as Reckoners.","[18] i.e., as small or insignificant as a mustard seed."
  21,48,"We certainly gave Moses and Aaron the Criterion, shining light and admonition<sup>19</sup> for the righteous,","[19] These are Torah’s three qualities."
  21,49,"those who fear their Lord without seeing Him<sup>20</sup>, and are apprehensive of the Hour.","[20] Or when they are in private and not seen by others."
  21,50,"And this [Qur’an] is a blessed reminder which We have sent down. Are you still denying it<sup>21</sup>?","[21] i.e., pretending ignorance or refusing to acknowledge it?"
  21,51,"Indeed, We had given Abraham sound judgment before<sup>22</sup>, for We know him well.","[22] i.e., before Moses, or in his early youth."
  21,52,"When he said to his father and his people, “What are these statues to which you are so devoted?”",""
  21,53,"They said, “We found our forefathers worshiping them.”",""
  21,54,"He said, “Indeed, you and your forefathers were clearly misguided.”",""
  21,55,"They said, “Have you come to us with the truth, or are you joking?”",""
  21,56,"He said, “Nay, your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and earth, Who created them, and I am one of those who bear witness to it.",""
  21,57,"By Allah, I will surely plot against your idols after you have turned and gone away.”",""
